Ticket Management System
This is a simple ticket management system that allows staff to create and respond to tickets, reopen closed tickets, and view ticket statistics.

Requirements
Python 3.x
ticket_maker.py
Getting Started
Clone the repository to your local machine.
Open your terminal or command prompt and navigate to the project directory.
Run the following command to start the program: python main.py

How to Use
Upon running the program, you will be presented with the main menu which allows you to choose from the following options:

Display all tickets
Submit a new ticket
Provide a response to a ticket
Reopen a ticket
Display ticket statistics
Exit the program
To create a new ticket, select option 2 and follow the prompts to provide the necessary information. If the issue description contains the word "password", a new password will be generated and provided in the ticket response.

To respond to a ticket, select option 3 and choose the ticket number you wish to respond to. Enter your response and the ticket will be marked as "CLOSED".

To reopen a closed ticket, select option 4 and choose the ticket number you wish to reopen.

To view ticket statistics, select option 5.
